storyInfo: Eunectes hurries back to Acahualla after receiving a letter from Inam to begin a construction project. Despite insisting that he would have no part of it, High Priest starts getting involved...

attributes.content: You're back, Zumama.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I read your letter. But shouldn't Gavial be dealing with the padishah's discovery of the Durins?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: It's not that bad. Well, not anymore.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I took a shipment of Durin ale to his court, and that kind of washed away the suspicion that the spies had planted in his mind. Now he's convinced it's just a bunch of drunkards who popped up in Acahualla and can brew decent ale.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Problem solved, then.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You're back too, High Priest.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Since when have I failed to come back after getting blown up?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You got blown up again?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Please, High Priest, don't interrupt.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: You hear that, Inam? Don't interrupt. Problem solved, everybody's happy.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You went off the rails first.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: ...Never mind.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Anyway, the ale went down so well with the padishah that he ordered Acahualla to 'start building things so it looks like people are actually living there and stop being an embarrassment to the satrapy'.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Now the Durins are busy building up their new settlement and don't have any time, so I had to call you back for the design. You think you can do it?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Zumama?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Those pretty steel buttresses by the lake...
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Oh, the steel-framed sand castle.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: It's a model of the new Zeruertza that Stitch built. The Durins loved it, and they're now modeling their new settlement after it.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Wow.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Wow is right. Now, as their neighbor, we need you even more.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: What did the Tiacauh say?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: No much, other than 'Bigger!' and 'Taller!'.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: The one who wanted bigger got into a fight with the one who wanted taller.
attributes.name: Deculture Silvermint

attributes.content: Who won?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Neither. It was a draw.
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: Anyway, the Tiacauh settlement is counting on you in order to compete with the Durins.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: You learned a bunch of stuff at Rhodes Island, didn't you? There's a different look in your eyes.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: What about me?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You? You're fine the way you are. You can help out when you're in the mood; when you're not in the mood, well, it's not like anyone's counting on you anyway.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: What? Did you hear what she said, girl?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Girl? Zumama? Operator Eunectes?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Eunectes does not hear a word.
She looks straight at 'New Zeruertza' by the lakeside. Perhaps she is admiring it, perhaps she is still processing the shock, or perhaps she is already thinking about competing with it.
Hmph! Well, if you put it that way, I'm not getting involved at all this time! You do whatever you want, and don't come begging for help if you screw up!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: A few days later...
You're still here, High Priest? Are you not helping Zumama design the new settlement?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I said she can do it on her own this time and it's none of my business. Your memory is lousy!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You've got a long memory for grudges.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I'm a man of my word.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But it's been a few days. Where's Zumama?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You could always check for yourself, if you're worried.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: No, na-ah, not going to happen. Your High Priest has got to lead by example.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Do you know what kind of settlement Zumama wants to build?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Wh-What kind?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Pfft.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Inam, how big of a project can Acahualla support with the resources we've got?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Well, I'm not sure how to answer that. What do you have in mind?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Bigger.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: And?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Taller.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: And?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: ...Let me think about it.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: So you didn't get an answer either!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: It needs to be bigger, and taller. Zumama said so.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I've already started gathering materials. Will you help?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I said it's none of my business.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: (Laughs) Suit yourself.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: A few days later...
Good morning.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Good morning, High Priest. Are you here for a bath?
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: No, just wanted to ask if the girl came to you lately.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Zumama? Yeah, she came.
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: How was she? Did she come begging for help with despair in her eyes, because Inam said what she designed wasn't realistic?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Not exactly...
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: Then what did she come for?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Croque, I wanted to ask, why haven't the Durins built a nomadic city, with all your advanced technology?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: A what city? You mean those massive things with wheels that run around, transforming into fighting robots when they bump into enemies?
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: Yeah, those.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Let me think... why, indeed?
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: Maybe it's because there are no enemies? Or the underground railroads are too narrow?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Those are both true, but I don't think they're the key reason... Thinking, thinking... maybe it wouldn't be profitable? No, people would gladly pay for something as cool as a city that turns into a fighting robot...
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: It must be because everyone is inside the city, so they don't get to see the city transform from the outside.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Yes! That must be it!
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: What do you mean, 'Yes! That must be it'? Isn't it because there's no Catastrophes underground?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: No what? Oh right, now I remember. People who come back from the surface say that's a thing.
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: You Durins are just as unreliable as the Tiacauh—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Wait, she's building a nomadic city?! Without me?!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Didn't you say you weren't helping? That's what Inam said.
attributes.name: Croque Diamondface

attributes.content: Th-That's none of your business!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But there's so much to do in order to build a nomadic city. It's not going to build itself while she shuts herself in a room, is it?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Yota, do you think we're spending too much time using fully automatic high-power saws? Should we spend some time working out?
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: Weren't you telling me to rest more a little while back? Hey, what's that below the high-pressure saw, it just showed up?
attributes.name: Yota

attributes.content: High-POWER saw.
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: No, it's the High Priest!
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: Now you're getting even worse. How did you get those mixed up?
attributes.name: Yota

attributes.content: It's 'high-power'. No 'r' after the 'p'.
attributes.name: Yota

attributes.content: I mean—
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: He means me.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Oh, hey, High Priest. Haven't seen you in a while.
attributes.name: Yota

attributes.content: Yes, it has been a while. I heard the girl summoned you yesterday?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Yeah—
attributes.name: Yota

attributes.content: No!
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: No?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: We didn't see Zumama.
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: Then who are you cutting down trees for.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Er...
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: Drop the act. More than one witness saw you meeting with Zumama. What did she say to you?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Oh, er, 'no man's city'!
attributes.name: Yota

attributes.content: First, we need wood.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Well, if you need trees cut down, you've come to the right guys. What kind of wood you need?
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: The thicker the better. Needs to bear a lot of weight.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: And don't tell anyone. Especially not the Durins.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Yogi

attributes.content: Ehm... they might not be happy about it. Better that I tell them myself.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: I knew it. She's building a nomadic city.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But why does she want wood that can bear a lot of weight? Is she trying to build a nomadic city out of wood? That's crazy.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: And what does it have to do with the Durins? They're not trying to build a nomadic city.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Wait... didn't Inam say she wanted the design to compete with the Durins'?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: A nomadic city is more impressive than buildings fixed to the ground, of course, but what the Tiacauh build won't look anywhere near as spectacular as Stitch's design...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: She's not trying to recreate that model by the lake on a mobile platform, is she? That's crazy, not even she would do that...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But if she did...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I got to stop her! She doesn't know what she's getting herself into!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: (Yawn) I must be hallucinating after spending too much time with the blueprints...
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Who are you calling a hallucination, kid?!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I thought you went back to Acahualla.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: You'll lose all your hair if you keep minding things that aren't your business.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: A nomadic city? In the jungle?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Let me see her plans.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Here.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: (Mumbles) Don't blame me for borrowing your old homework, girl. This is for the good of everyone.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Pretty standard stuff. When did she learn all this?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: ...Huh?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Do you know what these thick pipes are?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: And are these fists that I see on the diagram?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Gun barrels and robotic arms. There are also missile pods here.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: What about residential? Where are people going to live?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Underneath the guns, storage room, cockpit. Mostly under the guns, because there are plenty of those.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: ...That wasn't really intended as a question.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: I figured as much.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I'm almost touched that she gave serious thought to commercial infrastructure and transportation...
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Never mind that. I came to ask you for permission, Stitch, because this is serious.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Won't you let the girl copy your design?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You mean, build the exact settlement that I designed, except on a mobile platform?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: I know it might be hard to accept, but—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Sure.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: My design incorporates a lot of Acahuallan elements, and the Durins and Tiacauh living together was one of the things I considered.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: If Eunectes is okay with it, it's fine by me. I'm curious to see how she puts my design onto a mobile platform.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: (Mumbles) You'll probably faint when you see it.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But I have to ask, if Eunectes wants to build a nomadic city, why is the design basically a mobile fortress?
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Let's go shopping, Zumama.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: ...I'm going back.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: It's your first time setting foot on a nomadic city. Aren't you happy about it?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I was happy. I thought it would bring me one step closer to my dream.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: But I was wrong.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: The picture etched into my memory... what I really want, is a massive construct of steel moving slowly before my eyes.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Steel walls the height of a waterfall, gleaming metal brighter than the sun, treading trees that have stood for thousands of years into dust...
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Absolute strength. Absolute power. Nothing so... mundane.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: I see. It's not beauty she's looking for; it's power.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Exactly.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But that's not what she's like at Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Hm? She spends all day chatting with the robots at Rhodes Island. They're like sisters. It's pretty cute.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I don't think it's arbitrary—
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: Time for your checkup, Stitch! Are you coming out yourself, or do I have to come in and get you?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: G-Gavial?!
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: I-I'm coming out! Don't come in!
attributes.name: Minimalist

attributes.content: A few days later...
Anyway, the girl wants to replicate a Durin settlement and move it onto a mobile platform.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Well, the Durin problem was coming to a head sooner or later. Fast-tracking it isn't such a bad thing, just that it's maybe a little too conspicuous.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Maybe give it a bit of polish. Make the padishah dependent on us, rather than fearful of us...
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I have to say, Inam, as far as being a lord ameer is concerned, you're better than Gavial.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I'll take that as a compliment.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: How did you know all this? Couldn't resist talking to her?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Of course not. All the results of a painstaking investigation.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Anyway, now that we know what Zumama wants to do, we should help her deal with the aftermath. You can go, if there's nothing else you need.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Did you think I came to ask for help? No, I came to help you.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Follow me.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Ore vein? How did you find a place like this?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I used to live here. It turned into a mine after some geological changes.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: No wonder Zumama has a knack for finding all sorts of metals that I've never seen before.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: This is where The Big Ugly was built. It was abandoned after the girl decided to leave Acahualla.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Why did you bring me here?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Find a way to 'accidentally' discover this ore vein and offer it to the padishah. Should be enough to buy a nomadic city permit.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: That would be a bad deal, for you. The padishah would be the first to offer his support if we billed the nomadic city as a Durin brewing platform.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Deep breath, deep breath.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I appreciate it, though. It may not be useful right now, but it could come in handy in the future.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I have a question though.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Please, ask.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I've seen my fair share of eccentrics, but your mysteries might top them all.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Why did you suddenly show up with Zumama? How did you end up living with her, and even doing all this to help her?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Why?
The High Priest is used to this question from Zumama, but not from others.
Is it because Zumama was the first in the jungle to hold nuts and bolts in her hands?
Because, at heart, he is a lover of machines?
Because he was lonely for so long, and wanted someone interesting to talk to?
When developing The Big Ugly, she said to me...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: 'We'll make this machine together, and then you'll drive it, High Priest!'
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: That's a good story.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I like it too.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Then shouldn't you be helping her with the design?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Can't go back on my word. Besides, it's high time she stood on her own two feet.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Was that anger all an act?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Burdenbeast dung—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Yes or no?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Of course—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You have quite the mean streak in you. That's why you make a good lord ameer.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Alright, enough joking around. I really do think you should give Zumama a hand. I think they're almost ready to start.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Well... if you insist, I'll go back on my word, this once.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: She's not in?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Not in her room, at least.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: What about Yogi and Yota? They might know something.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: The neighbors said they went out early.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Hey, do you know where Zumama, Yogi and Yota went?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: What's Zumama doing here?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I remember this place—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: High Priest? Inam? What are you doing here?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Worried about you—ahem, ahem.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Why are you wearing protective gear? And the direction you came from is...?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: The ruins of Zeruertza.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Why did you go there?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: The dust disperses, and the High Priest sees what is in the carts behind Eunectes.
You were picking up junk in the ruins of Zeruertza?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: It's not junk! Look, a Durin door frame! It took a ton of work to get it out from under the rubble!
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: And this is part of the Great Aquapit slide. I couldn't bring the whole thing back, so I cut off the bottom part, which had the most interesting design.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: That's the definition of junk! I thought you were bringing Stitch's New Zeruertza design onto a mobile platform!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: What? Why? It's a competition. What's the point of doing what the Durins are doing?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Weren't you worried that the Durins would be unhappy?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I was going into the ruins of Zeruertza, after all. It was their home, even if it was destroyed.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: But I asked Deculture and she said I could take anything I wanted.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: The reason you had Yogi and Yota cut trees...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I needed a decent cart to bring this stuff back.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Don't tell me you weren't planning to build a nomadic city at all?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: (Stifles laughter) How about we go back and you take your time to tell us what your plan is?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: There's no need for that. The High Priest just said it, I'm building a nomadic city.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Really?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Really.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Phew. Well, what do you have to say now, Inam?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: What do I have to say? It's not like I said anything.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Hmph. Forget that black-hearted lord ameer; how do you plan to build a nomadic city? With this junk that you dug up from underground?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Yeah, but that's not important. What's really important is—
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Model R3-E3 Assistant Robot #0332, reporting in.
attributes.name: Strange Machine A

attributes.content: Model R3-E3 Assistant Robot #0719, reporting in.
attributes.name: Strange Machine B
Strange Machine C
attributes.content: Model R3-E3 Assistant Robot #0086,

attributes.name: Strange Machine C
attributes.content: rererereporporpor—
So you went to save your friends...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Not entirely.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Here's what I think. The nomadic city of the Tiacauh needs to be ahead of its time. It needs to be incredible.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: As far as design is concerned, I could never compete with Stitch.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: That's why I'm building a living city.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: My friends here, once fixed, will become the building blocks of the new city.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: The robots will be your city's building blocks? And then?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Three friends make one large unit, and five large units make one huge unit, unit after unit, until they're the size of a nomadic city!
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: That way, you can get an answer no matter which part of the city you talk to, and the whole nomadic city will be friends with the people living inside it!
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Okay... where will the people live?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Don't worry, I've thought about it. Here are the blueprints.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: I'll just look past the multitude of problems right now. Problem after problem, yet somehow it might just work.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I think it'll work.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: First, though, you need to tell me what's going on with this shape.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: It's absolute madness. One domed roof, three pairs of wheels, medical equipment...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: A city-sized—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Lancet-2?!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: She makes a cute big sister, doesn't she?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Look at the last page of the plans.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: I've got everything thought out. A supercomputer in the center of the city, controlling all the robot friends.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: I made the connector round so that Lancet-2 can sit in it—
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: What about me?!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Didn't you give a single thought about me when designing this city?! After all the worrying I did for your sake?!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: You know what, screw it, do whatever you want, it's none of my business, I'm going on a long trip—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Your room's here, High Priest.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: What's this? Way out in a corner? This isn't the least bit cool compared to that round supercomputer connector! And it's right next to a warehouse—
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: That's my bedroom.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: You'll be right next door to me. You can come visit any time.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: High Priest is at a loss for words. Inam can no longer stifle her laughter.
Well, how about it? Will you help Zumama or not?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Finally, the High Priest comes to terms with his emotions and composes himself, even finding the wherewithal to give his ridiculous glasses a little pompous push.
Of course I'm helping.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: First step will be a trip to Rhodes Island on your behalf.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: For what?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: To ask the subject of your blueprints...
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Whether the robot who won't even let you drink coffee will let you do this.
attributes.name: High Priest
